<br>
I wish I was here for a happier post.  I wish a lot of things...  Not all come true.  However I'll get to the point, this is not as easy as I thought...<br>
<br>
On October 26th of this year it will be exactly 1 year to the day that Poper/Justin Sherwood left us suddenly.  It's been a long hard year, especially for his parents Deb &amp; Gar.<br>
<br>
Deb &amp; Gar will be in the U.S. for this day as staying home is just to hard for them.  <br>
<br>
The family has asked that to remember him we write a little note to Justin, put it in a helium baloon and release it Oct 26th 9:00 PM EST.  Anyone wishing to participate is most welcome, worldwide.  You could also send a little note to Deb &amp; Gar at: dsherwoood@rogers.com (Note the 3 O's in the last name)  if you cc: kirby03@canada.com they will also get a copy of the email while they are on the road.<br>
<br>
I urge anyone that remembers Justin to send a quick email to his parents, it would mean more than you can image to them, that people would take the time to remember Justin.<br>
<br>
Guild Leaders.  If you can, I would ask for 1 minute of silence on Oct 26th @ 9:00 PM EST as a small dedicated to a person that went well above and beyond his years to help so many.  I would truly appriciate this.<br>
<br>
Rick.<br>
